Researchers write abstracts in their own vocabulary.
Top-cited papers in the same field use different keywords.
This tool shows exactly what's missing from yours.

Live Tool
research-impact-copilot.vercel.app
Free to use. I don't store your paper anywhere.

What It Does
Paste your title and abstract. The tool queries the 
top 20 most-cited papers in your field on OpenAlex 
(480M+ papers) and returns:

- Keywords those papers use that yours is missing
- How many of the top 20 papers contain each keyword
- Average citations behind each keyword
- An optimized title suggestion using the gap keywords

Why I Built This
My father is a pharmaceutical researcher with 858 
citations and an h-index of 18. His newer papers 
weren't getting found despite strong research. I 
couldn't find a free tool that showed which keywords 
were actually driving citations in his field. So I 
built one.

How It Works
1. Paste your paper title and abstract
2. Tool queries OpenAlex for top cited papers in your 
   detected research field
3. Returns keyword gap analysis with real citation data

Stack
- Backend: FastAPI (Python)
- Frontend: Vanilla HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- Data: OpenAlex API (free, 480M+ papers)
- Deployed: Render (backend) + Vercel (frontend)

Honest Disclaimer
This tool shows which keywords top-cited papers use. 
It does not guarantee more citations. Citation growth 
depends on research quality, journal choice, and 
distribution. This is one signal, not a complete 
solution.

